<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 22 at 12:34AM CST  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of western Pushmataha,
western Latimer and southeastern Pittsburg Counties through 115 AM
CST...
At 1234 AM CST, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from near Kiowa to 5 miles east of Lane. Movement was
northeast at 55 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects.
Locations in or near the path include...
Wilburton...                      Clayton...
Hartshorne...                     Kiowa...
Snow...                           Higgins...
Stanley...                        Kellond...
Clayton Lake State Park...        Damon...
Yanush...                         Robbers Cave State Park...
Moyers...                         Kosoma...
Dunbar...                         Blanco...
Haileyville...                    Pittsburg...
Gowen...                          Darwin...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 400 AM CST for southeastern
Oklahoma.</instruction>
